**Overview**

This report provides an analysis of pesticide usage for the selected active ingredients across Canadian provinces and regions. The data includes information on quantities, geographic distribution, and key insights.

Geographical Distribution Interactive Map

knitr::opts_chunk$set(echo = TRUE)
leaflet(filtered_data) %>%
  addTiles() %>%
  addCircles(
    lng = ~longitude, lat = ~latitude,
    weight = 1, radius = ~kg_imp_total / max(kg_imp_total, na.rm = TRUE) * 500000,
    popup = ~paste("<strong>Region:</strong>", full_name,
                   "<br><strong>Active Ingredient:</strong>", active_name,
                   "<br><strong>Kg Imported:</strong>", round(kg_imp_total, 2)),
    color = ~colorNumeric("YlOrRd", kg_imp_total)(kg_imp_total),
    opacity = 0.8, fillOpacity = 0.6
  ) %>%
  addLegend("bottomright", pal = colorNumeric("YlOrRd", filtered_data$kg_imp_total),
            values = ~kg_imp_total, title = "Kg Imported") %>%
  addFullscreenControl()

Visual Analysis Bar Chart of Pesticide Usage by Region

knitr::opts_chunk$set(echo = TRUE)
ggplot(filtered_data, aes(x = region, y = kg_imp_total, fill = active_name)) +
  geom_bar(stat = "identity", position = "dodge") +
  theme_minimal() +
  labs(
    title = "Pesticide Usage by Region",
    x = "Region",
    y = "Kg Imported",
    fill = "Active Ingredient"
  ) +
  theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 45, hjust = 1))

Insights and Recommendations Key Insight: Areas with high usage of certain active ingredients may require targeted regulatory compliance efforts or educational outreach. Recommendation: Leverage these insights to optimize pesticide usage patterns, promote sustainable practices, and minimize environmental impact.
